Resides in the underworld, Tartarus. Hecate (hekate) was knowen as being the goddess of sorcery &amp; silverfooted queen of the night. Skilled in the divine arts of foretelling the future she gives humans dreams and visions which interpeted wisely led to greater clarity.<br>
She wore a shimmering headdress she was...<br>
            SECOND TO NONE IN HER POWERS  <br>
Crowns herself with oak leaves and twisting coils of wild serpents her charriot pulled by dragons. Her image stands at crossroads where offerings of dogs, honey &amp; black lambs are left on full moon night.<br>
<br>
ANIMAL &amp; TREE SACRED TO HER:<br>
         ANIMAL~Dog<br>
             TREE~WILLOW<br>
She is connected with death &amp; regeneration. Her presence in the underworld allows for pre-Hellenic hope of re-birth and transformation as oppose to Hades who represents the inevitability of death.<br>
<br>
Hecate (Hekate) did not interfere when the maiden Persephone was dragged down to the underworld though she was one of the few who heard her screams <br>
