<br>
“I know of no other Greeks [than the Spartans sacrivices to Enyalios] who are accustomed to sacrifice puppies except the people of Kolophon; these too sacrifice a puppy, a black bitch, to Enodio (The Wayside Goddess). Both the sacrifice of the Kolophonians and that of the youths at Sparta are appointed to take place at night.” –Pausanias 3.14.9-10<br>
